# LLM Caller Configuration Example
# Copy this file to .env and configure your provider credentials

# ============================================================================
# PROVIDER API KEYS
# ============================================================================
# Configure at least one provider to enable LLM functionality

# OpenAI Configuration
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-api-key-here

# Anthropic Configuration
# Get your API key from: https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-anthropic-api-key-here

# LMStudio (Local Models) Configuration
# Install LMStudio from: https://lmstudio.ai/
# Load any models you want to use in LMStudio
# Start the local server in LMStudio before using
# The system will auto-discover all loaded models and select the best one for each task
LMSTUDIO_BASE_URL=http://localhost:1234/v1

# ============================================================================
# SERVICE SETTINGS
# ============================================================================

# Service host and port (for server mode)
LLM_CALLER_HOST=localhost
LLM_CALLER_PORT=8080

# Privacy Mode: Prefer local models when available
# Set to 'true' to prioritize LMStudio over cloud providers
LLM_CALLER_PREFER_LOCAL=false

# ============================================================================
# USAGE INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Choose your provider strategy:
#
#    Option A - Cloud Only (OpenAI/Anthropic):
#      - Uncomment and set OPENAI_API_KEY or ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#      - Leave LMSTUDIO_BASE_URL commented or remove it
#      - Set LLM_CALLER_PREFER_LOCAL=false
#
#    Option B - Local Only (Privacy-First):
#      - Install and start LMStudio
#      - Load one or more models in LMStudio (e.g., Llama, Mistral, CodeLlama)
#      - Uncomment and set LMSTUDIO_BASE_URL
#      - Set LLM_CALLER_PREFER_LOCAL=true
#      - Comment out cloud provider keys
#      - System will auto-discover all loaded models via /v1/models API
#
#    Option C - Hybrid (Best of Both):
#      - Configure both cloud and local providers
#      - Set LLM_CALLER_PREFER_LOCAL based on your preference
#      - System will use local when available, fallback to cloud
#
# 3. Validate your configuration:
#    python llm_cli.py config --validate
#
# 4. Test the service:
#    python llm_cli.py status
#    python llm_cli.py chat "Hello, world!"
#
# ============================================================================
# INTELLIGENT MODEL ROUTING
# ============================================================================
#
# The LLM Caller includes an intelligent routing engine that automatically:
#
# 1. **Auto-Discovery**: Detects all available models from configured providers
#    - LMStudio: Queries /v1/models endpoint to discover loaded models
#    - OpenAI: Uses known model list (gpt-4, gpt-3.5-turbo, etc.)
#    - Anthropic: Uses known model list (claude-3-opus, claude-3-sonnet, etc.)
#
# 2. **Task Detection**: Analyzes your request to determine the task type:
#    - Code generation/analysis
#    - Document summarization
#    - Creative writing
#    - Data analysis
#    - General conversation
#
# 3. **Best Model Selection**: Chooses the optimal model based on:
#    - Task type (e.g., CodeLlama for coding, GPT-4 for complex reasoning)
#    - Context length requirements
#    - Provider availability
#    - Local preference setting (LLM_CALLER_PREFER_LOCAL)
#    - Model capabilities and performance characteristics
#
# 4. **Automatic Fallback**: If the selected model fails, tries alternatives
#
# Examples:
#   - "Write a Python function" → Routes to CodeLlama (if local) or GPT-4
#   - "Summarize this document" → Routes to GPT-3.5 or local Mistral
#   - "Explain this code" → Routes to best available code-focused model
#
# You don't need to specify models manually - the system picks the best one!
# (But you can override with --model flag if needed)
#
# ============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================================================
#
# - Never commit .env to version control
# - .env is in .gitignore by default
# - Keep your API keys secret
# - Rotate keys regularly
# - Use local models for sensitive data
#
